6.7.3 Basic Properties of /\ and \/

Exercise 27. Prove (P /\ ((Q \/ R) \/ Q)) /\ S = S /\ ((R \/ Q) /\ P).

Proof by equational reasoning.

(P /\ ((Q \/ R) \/ Q)) /\ S
  = (P /\ ((R \/ Q) \/ Q)) /\ S     {\/ commutative}
  = (P /\ (R \/ (Q \/ Q))) /\ S     {\/ associative}
  = (P /\ (R \/ Q)) /\ S            {\/ indempotent}
  = ((R \/ Q) /\ P) /\ S            {/\ commutative}
  = S /\ ((R \/ Q) /\ P)            {/\ commutative}

QED

Exercise 28. Prove P /\ (Q /\ (R /\ S)) = ((P /\ Q) /\ R) /\ S.

Proof by equational reasoning.

P /\ (Q /\ (R /\ S))
  = P /\ ((Q /\ R) /\ S)            {/\ associative}
  = (P /\ (Q /\ R)) /\ S            {/\ associative}
  = ((P /\ Q) /\ R) /\ S            {/\ associative}

